# Exclude heavy / sensitive paths from the Docker build context. The api
# Dockerfile uses `context: ..` (repo root) so without this every byte in
# the working tree — including node_modules, .git, dist, logs, env files —
# would be copied to the daemon before the build runs. With this in place,
# context transfers drop by an order of magnitude on cold builds.

# Dependencies
node_modules
**/node_modules
.pnpm-store

# Build outputs (created inside Docker)
**/dist
**/build

# TypeScript build info
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/.tsbuildinfo

# Test / coverage artifacts
**/coverage
**/.vitest
**/.nyc_output

# Source control / IDE
.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.idea

# Documentation / misc
docs
**/*.md
README.md
LICENSE
.editorconfig

# Local config & secrets
.env
.env.local
**/.env
!**/.env.example

# Logs / temp
**/*.log
**/tmp
**/.cache
**/.turbo

# OS noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Tests folder is rebuilt inside the container if needed
**/test
**/tests
